<p>
phpMyAdmin security announcement
</p>
<hr>
<p>
Announcement-ID: PMASA-2007-8<br />
Date: 2007-11-20<br />
</p>
<p>
<b>Summary</b>:<br />
XSS vulnerability
</p>
<p>
<b>Description</b>:<br />
We received an advisory from Tim Brown, Nth Dimension, and we wish to thank him for his work. The login page (auth_type cookie) was vulnerable to XSS via the convcharset parameter.<br /></br />
</p>
<p>
<b>Severity</b>:<br />
We consider this vulnerability to be serious.
</p>
<p>
<b>Affected versions</b>:<br />
Probably all versions before 2.11.2.2. 
</p>
<p>
<b>Solution:</b><br />
Upgrade to phpMyAdmin 2.11.2.2 or newer.
</p>
<p>
<b>References:</b><br />
<a href="http://www.nth-dimension.org.uk/downloads.php?id=38">http://www.nth-dimension.org.uk/downloads.php?id=38</a>
<br /><br />
The patch is attached to:
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1835123&group_id=23067&atid=377408">http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1835123&group_id=23067&atid=377408</a>
</p>
<p>
For further information and in case of questions, please contact the
phpMyAdmin team. Our website is <a href="http://www.phpmyadmin.net">http://www.phpmyadmin.net/</a>.
</p>
